select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` in (1) and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\\Models\\User'

select count(*) as aggregate from (select `rcms`.*, `deptos`.`nombredepto` as `nombredepto`, `municipios`.`nombremunicipio` as `nombremunicipio`, `users`.`name` as `username` from `rcms` inner join `deptos` on `deptos`.`id` = `rcms`.`iddepto` inner join `municipios` on `municipios`.`id` = `rcms`.`idmunicipio` inner join `users` on `rcms`.`created_by` = `users`.`id` order by `rcms`.`id` desc) count_row_table

select `rcms`.*, `deptos`.`nombredepto` as `nombredepto`, `municipios`.`nombremunicipio` as `nombremunicipio`, `users`.`name` as `username` from `rcms` inner join `deptos` on `deptos`.`id` = `rcms`.`iddepto` inner join `municipios` on `municipios`.`id` = `rcms`.`idmunicipio` inner join `users` on `rcms`.`created_by` = `users`.`id` order by `rcms`.`id` desc, `codigo` desc limit 25 offset 0
